WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:03.544
Margin based campaigns in Google is a broken strategy

00:00:03.545 --> 00:00:05.528
and I'm here to tell you why they don't

00:00:05.529 --> 00:00:07.448
work and what you should do instead.

00:00:07.449 --> 00:00:09.872
Margin based campaigns are still not only being

00:00:09.873 --> 00:00:12.000
run in Google Ad accounts, but are still

00:00:12.001 --> 00:00:15.592
being recommended by people, which just constantly surprises

00:00:15.593 --> 00:00:17.696
me because the foundation for that type of

00:00:17.697 --> 00:00:20.120
campaign structure is just full of holes.

00:00:20.121 --> 00:00:22.256
Margin based campaigns is this thing where

00:00:22.257 --> 00:00:23.992
you set up different Google shopping campaigns

00:00:23.993 --> 00:00:27.184
or different PMAX campaigns for different groups

00:00:27.185 --> 00:00:28.816
of products based on their margin.

00:00:28.817 --> 00:00:31.048
It'll typically look something like this.

00:00:31.049 --> 00:00:34.952
You have a high margin campaign targeting 300% ROAS, you

00:00:34.953 --> 00:00:38.312
have a mid margin campaign targeting 500% ROAS, and you

00:00:38.313 --> 00:00:42.048
have a low margin campaign targeting at 700% ROAS.

00:00:42.049 --> 00:00:44.312
Whatever these targets are, it doesn't really matter.

00:00:44.313 --> 00:00:46.120
But basically what we're trying to do here is

00:00:46.121 --> 00:00:49.928
you're trying to bid high for high margin product

00:00:49.929 --> 00:00:52.272
and thereby get a lot of volume, maximize revenue.

00:00:52.273 --> 00:00:54.288
And for the lower margin products, you're basically

00:00:54.289 --> 00:00:56.832
trying to protect them so they're not unprofitable.

00:00:56.833 --> 00:00:59.924
Having all these products in the same

00:00:59.925 --> 00:01:02.708
campaign is on paper really bad.

00:01:02.709 --> 00:01:04.916
And it makes a lot of sense to break them

00:01:04.917 --> 00:01:07.732
up because obviously you want to get, you want to

00:01:07.733 --> 00:01:10.524
protect your lower margin products from not overspending.

00:01:10.525 --> 00:01:11.700
Plus you want to get as much

00:01:11.701 --> 00:01:13.812
out of your high margin products.

00:01:13.813 --> 00:01:17.364
The problem is that it assumes the consumers buy

00:01:17.365 --> 00:01:19.204
what they click on, which isn't the case.

00:01:19.205 --> 00:01:22.260
I've done this analysis in many, many accounts and

00:01:22.261 --> 00:01:25.220
every single time I review it, at least 3,50%

00:01:25.221 --> 00:01:28.364
of consumers buy a completely different brand or completely

00:01:28.365 --> 00:01:31.284
different category than the product that they clicked on.

00:01:31.285 --> 00:01:34.084
The second problem is that the way that Google reports

00:01:34.085 --> 00:01:37.716
on this, many assume that because Google show clicks and

00:01:37.717 --> 00:01:41.604
conversions tied back to the individual product or item id,

00:01:41.605 --> 00:01:43.756
then it's showing what people actually bought.

00:01:43.757 --> 00:01:44.892
This is also wrong.

00:01:44.893 --> 00:01:47.716
Google reports on what products were clicked on,

00:01:47.717 --> 00:01:49.868
not the product that was actually bought.

00:01:49.869 --> 00:01:52.188
Although you can expand your conversion tracking with cart

00:01:52.189 --> 00:01:54.588
data and get all this information, it still doesn't

00:01:54.589 --> 00:01:57.672
change my point of view on margin based campaigns.

00:01:57.673 --> 00:01:58.976
The third problem is that

00:01:58.977 --> 00:02:00.592
you're splitting up your data.

00:02:00.593 --> 00:02:02.816
If you have a thousand conversions a month, then

00:02:02.817 --> 00:02:04.816
it's not, it's not a super big deal.

00:02:04.817 --> 00:02:07.376
But anything below a thousand conversions per

00:02:07.377 --> 00:02:09.464
month and smart bidding starts underperforming.

00:02:09.465 --> 00:02:11.456
Maybe it's not an issue for some of

00:02:11.457 --> 00:02:16.880
your campaigns, but across all, across all three

00:02:16.881 --> 00:02:19.024
margin based campaigns, it can be a problem.

00:02:19.025 --> 00:02:20.864
Let's take this example for.

00:02:20.865 --> 00:02:22.960
Let's take this as an example.

00:02:22.961 --> 00:02:24.734
You have 1000 conversions in total.

00:02:24.735 --> 00:02:28.142
You have 500 in your mid margin campaigns, you

00:02:28.143 --> 00:02:30.446
have 350 in your high margin campaign, but you

00:02:30.447 --> 00:02:33.790
only have 150 in your low margin campaign which

00:02:33.791 --> 00:02:36.046
also has a pretty high roas target.

00:02:36.047 --> 00:02:38.542
Suddenly smart bidding is having an awful lot

00:02:38.543 --> 00:02:40.782
of trouble optimizing your low margin campaign.

00:02:40.783 --> 00:02:42.526
With a high roas target and

00:02:42.527 --> 00:02:44.350
only five conversions a day.

00:02:44.351 --> 00:02:48.302
This results in a lower overall performance because again,

00:02:48.303 --> 00:02:51.406
just splitting up all your data, some of your

00:02:51.407 --> 00:02:53.470
campaigns will have very, very little data to work

00:02:53.471 --> 00:02:55.690
based on and that can hu the performance.

00:02:55.691 --> 00:02:58.906
So even though you are going from 1,000 conversions and

00:02:58.907 --> 00:03:01.850
splitting those up, you might end up having those 150

00:03:01.851 --> 00:03:04.666
conversions in your low margin campaign actually end up being

00:03:04.667 --> 00:03:08.010
120 or 110 or not hitting the row start you

00:03:08.011 --> 00:03:11.210
actually intended it to be just because the system has

00:03:11.211 --> 00:03:12.970
less data to work with.

00:03:12.971 --> 00:03:14.690
So what works best instead?

00:03:14.691 --> 00:03:17.338
There's two ways to go about this.

00:03:17.339 --> 00:03:19.850
One is consolidate campaigns into high and low

00:03:19.851 --> 00:03:22.930
margin to retain as much data as possible.

00:03:22.931 --> 00:03:25.426
You just need to acknowledge that you

00:03:25.427 --> 00:03:28.310
can't 100% know what people buy.

00:03:29.250 --> 00:03:30.730
But it's better than nothing.

00:03:30.731 --> 00:03:32.514
If you truly have two different

00:03:32.515 --> 00:03:36.266
categories like speakers and a couch.

00:03:36.267 --> 00:03:37.490
And a couch you have 10%

00:03:37.491 --> 00:03:39.738
margin and the speaker 50% margin.

00:03:39.739 --> 00:03:41.986
You can kind of know that people are not going

00:03:41.987 --> 00:03:44.162
to jump from one category to the other there.

00:03:44.163 --> 00:03:46.154
But if it is that you have 10, 20, 30,

00:03:46.155 --> 00:03:49.090
40, 50 different brands within one category and they all

00:03:49.091 --> 00:03:53.862
have very different margins, then it's a very, very flawed

00:03:53.863 --> 00:03:56.290
strategy to use a margin based campaign.

00:03:56.830 --> 00:04:00.174
So the actual proper way to fix this

00:04:00.175 --> 00:04:02.742
is to implement a gross profit tracking method.

00:04:02.743 --> 00:04:05.246
Or it's also, you can also

00:04:05.247 --> 00:04:06.742
say you're tracking contribution margin.

00:04:06.743 --> 00:04:09.774
It depends like I say gross profit, while others

00:04:09.775 --> 00:04:12.358
call it profit, some call it pos like profit

00:04:12.359 --> 00:04:15.062
on ad spend, some call contribution margin.

00:04:15.063 --> 00:04:16.814
It's kind of all the same thing.

00:04:16.815 --> 00:04:18.526
What we're in essence what we're trying to do

00:04:18.527 --> 00:04:20.766
is we're trying to track the gross profit from

00:04:20.767 --> 00:04:23.830
a sale instead of revenue, which, which means that

00:04:23.831 --> 00:04:26.622
you bypass the need to run margin based campaigns.

00:04:26.623 --> 00:04:29.486
Each transaction tells Google exactly what margin

00:04:29.487 --> 00:04:33.102
or contribution, contribution margin or gross profit

00:04:33.103 --> 00:04:34.846
that's derived from that transaction.

00:04:34.847 --> 00:04:37.030
So it knows that product A has a low

00:04:37.031 --> 00:04:39.430
margin and product B has high margin which it

00:04:39.431 --> 00:04:42.310
can use to set the bids accordingly because it

00:04:42.311 --> 00:04:44.806
gets the data right from the get go.

00:04:44.807 --> 00:04:46.230
If we take this example, then

00:04:46.231 --> 00:04:49.168
gross profit is calculated like this.

00:04:49.169 --> 00:04:52.904
So what we right now sending to Google is just revenue.

00:04:52.905 --> 00:04:55.056
On the other hand, if we send in

00:04:55.057 --> 00:04:57.616
profit or gross profit or contribution margin, then

00:04:57.617 --> 00:05:01.280
we're sending in revenue minus Discounts minus cost

00:05:01.281 --> 00:05:04.184
of goods sold, minus shipping costs, minor payment

00:05:04.185 --> 00:05:06.460
cost, minus packaging and handling.

00:05:07.120 --> 00:05:09.600
And this is such a monumentally better way

00:05:09.601 --> 00:05:12.656
to implement a nuanced biz bidding method when

00:05:12.657 --> 00:05:14.792
you have different margins for different products.

00:05:14.793 --> 00:05:17.274
Profit based bidding like this allows

00:05:17.275 --> 00:05:18.710
you to do several things.

00:05:19.730 --> 00:05:22.194
One, it track what roas level

00:05:22.195 --> 00:05:24.730
drives the highest profit in volume.

00:05:24.731 --> 00:05:28.298
Instead of an arbitrary number like roas, it allows

00:05:28.299 --> 00:05:30.754
smart bidding to bid higher for high margin products

00:05:30.755 --> 00:05:34.050
and keywords, segments, devices and all that.

00:05:34.051 --> 00:05:35.578
And it gives you insight to exactly

00:05:35.579 --> 00:05:37.130
when you lose money on a sale.

00:05:37.131 --> 00:05:40.370
We in savvy use this to know how

00:05:40.371 --> 00:05:41.978
low we can actually go for an upper

00:05:41.979 --> 00:05:44.770
funnel keyword before we start actually losing money.

00:05:44.771 --> 00:05:46.082
It helps drive a ton of

00:05:46.083 --> 00:05:48.478
growth when implemented the right way.

00:05:48.479 --> 00:05:51.806
So to compare this the right way, the things that

00:05:51.807 --> 00:05:54.134
I say is the right way at least is profit

00:05:54.135 --> 00:05:56.838
based bidding tracks what actually happens in a transaction.

00:05:56.839 --> 00:06:00.126
It also tracks how many products are in there.

00:06:00.127 --> 00:06:03.974
It tracks if you have a high margin, low margin

00:06:03.975 --> 00:06:06.694
product in the same cart, et cetera, et cetera.

00:06:06.695 --> 00:06:09.310
And the wrong way today as I believe it is,

00:06:09.311 --> 00:06:12.654
the margin based campaigns track what people click on, but

00:06:12.655 --> 00:06:14.950
it doesn't show what people actually end up buying.

00:06:14.951 --> 00:06:16.638
So you don't get the effect

00:06:16.639 --> 00:06:18.640
you're actually trying to get.

00:06:18.641 --> 00:06:24.152
So the problems that I have with profit tracking or contribution margin

00:06:24.153 --> 00:06:27.760
tracking is that when you run a sale like 10% off, 20%

00:06:27.761 --> 00:06:32.096
off, 30% off, the changes in data can hurt a lot in

00:06:32.097 --> 00:06:35.208
terms of how smart bidding works because all of a sudden it's

00:06:35.209 --> 00:06:38.672
used to saying, let's say you get $100 in value, all of

00:06:38.673 --> 00:06:40.944
a sudden it gets 80 or 70.

00:06:40.945 --> 00:06:44.810
So in essence the ROAS that it works based

00:06:44.811 --> 00:06:47.034
off just drops from one day to another.

00:06:47.035 --> 00:06:50.650
And doesn't know why that's a problem because like during

00:06:50.651 --> 00:06:52.866
a sale we actually wanted to drive more volume.

00:06:52.867 --> 00:06:55.346
So that can really be a challenge.

00:06:55.347 --> 00:06:56.810
Now there's ways to get around this.

00:06:56.811 --> 00:06:59.226
Conversion rate goes up during a sale, so

00:06:59.227 --> 00:07:00.922
all of a sudden it performs better.

00:07:00.923 --> 00:07:03.066
But for some businesses that run a lot of

00:07:03.067 --> 00:07:05.554
sales, this is a really big issue because smart

00:07:05.555 --> 00:07:08.882
bidding doesn't have this stable data anymore.

00:07:08.883 --> 00:07:10.706
The second thing is that very low margin

00:07:10.707 --> 00:07:13.242
businesses might have so little data that it

00:07:13.243 --> 00:07:14.362
becomes really hard to work with.

00:07:14.363 --> 00:07:15.410
Smart bidd.

00:07:15.411 --> 00:07:20.862
So if you consistently run at 120% profit on Aspen

00:07:20.863 --> 00:07:24.726
or POAS or ROAS, target changing to from 120 to

00:07:24.727 --> 00:07:28.646
115 or 110, it's basically cutting your profit in half.

00:07:28.647 --> 00:07:32.790
But Google Ads have like it's such a Small

00:07:32.791 --> 00:07:36.650
change for Google Ads going from 120% to 110%.

00:07:37.190 --> 00:07:38.486
So it can really be tough to

00:07:38.487 --> 00:07:40.102
work with smart baming at that level.

00:07:40.103 --> 00:07:43.766
It can also for some people I found it now

00:07:43.767 --> 00:07:46.166
that they can see the profit from every sale, then

00:07:46.167 --> 00:07:49.698
they start being way too focused on profitability and like

00:07:49.699 --> 00:07:52.226
every single day or week where they're not hitting a

00:07:52.227 --> 00:07:55.890
certain profit level in a Google Ads account, then they

00:07:55.891 --> 00:07:58.138
just, they just, they just go crazy.

00:07:58.139 --> 00:08:01.650
They, they just, they decrease bids, decrease bids to

00:08:01.651 --> 00:08:04.154
try to be more profitable and their volume goes

00:08:04.155 --> 00:08:06.970
down and it just hurts everything here. It's, it's.

00:08:06.971 --> 00:08:09.066
You need to also use something like a blended

00:08:09.067 --> 00:08:12.150
roas, new customers or any other data point.

00:08:13.100 --> 00:08:14.796
Also I would like to say if you

00:08:14.797 --> 00:08:17.396
have the same margin on all products, unnecessary.

00:08:17.397 --> 00:08:21.116
If you have the same margin on like 90% of your

00:08:21.117 --> 00:08:25.020
revenue, it still doesn't matter to do any of these things.

00:08:25.021 --> 00:08:27.180
It's just unnecessary to do.

00:08:27.181 --> 00:08:29.428
Last thing I wanted to mention is Google has a profit

00:08:29.429 --> 00:08:31.756
based betting in beta at the moment and it should come

00:08:31.757 --> 00:08:36.476
out during the early days of the early months of 2025.

00:08:36.477 --> 00:08:37.916
But it opens three issues.

00:08:37.917 --> 00:08:40.916
You can't troubleshoot it like you can yourself

00:08:40.917 --> 00:08:44.600
or with an A software like Profit Metrics.

00:08:45.320 --> 00:08:48.136
If I put on my tinfoil hat, then you

00:08:48.137 --> 00:08:51.856
also give Google your cogs and exact margins.

00:08:51.857 --> 00:08:53.536
This is a tinfoil hat theory.

00:08:53.537 --> 00:08:55.160
But I'm very worried about what

00:08:55.161 --> 00:08:56.208
that can do to your auction.

00:08:56.209 --> 00:08:59.660
If Google knows exactly how hard to squeeze you

00:09:00.440 --> 00:09:02.376
and it doesn't account for things like shipping and

00:09:02.377 --> 00:09:04.432
handling, they're minor things in the bigger picture.

00:09:04.433 --> 00:09:06.936
But for some businesses it's important to

00:09:06.937 --> 00:09:09.640
calculate that as part of their profitability.

00:09:09.641 --> 00:09:13.208
So to summarize before we go to actions from here,

00:09:13.209 --> 00:09:15.840
what consumers click on does not equal what they end

00:09:15.841 --> 00:09:19.232
up buying or adding to the cart alongside the product.

00:09:19.233 --> 00:09:21.288
Splitting your data into multiple campaigns

00:09:21.289 --> 00:09:23.048
is not ideal for smart bidding.

00:09:23.049 --> 00:09:25.328
Only a lot of data can allow this to work.

00:09:25.329 --> 00:09:27.200
So that's why margin based campaigns can actually

00:09:27.201 --> 00:09:30.368
hurt your performance better than improving it.

00:09:30.369 --> 00:09:32.720
Profit based bidding with a software like something

00:09:32.721 --> 00:09:34.960
like Profit Metrics gives smart bidding much better

00:09:34.961 --> 00:09:38.016
data to bid directly on profit which can

00:09:38.017 --> 00:09:39.700
open up for much better performance.

00:09:40.250 --> 00:09:42.266
Profit based bidding is not just applicable to

00:09:42.267 --> 00:09:45.242
shopping, but works well with shopping as well,

00:09:45.243 --> 00:09:48.186
which everybody seems to ignore in this thing.

00:09:48.187 --> 00:09:50.650
So if we put up a margin based campaign for

00:09:50.651 --> 00:09:52.754
shopping, why don't we do the same thing for search?

00:09:52.755 --> 00:09:54.650
Why don't we do set different targets for them?

00:09:54.651 --> 00:09:58.050
Most people just ignore that and you avoid

00:09:58.051 --> 00:10:00.746
all of this margin based campaign structure which

00:10:00.747 --> 00:10:02.882
opens the door to create a more sophisticated

00:10:02.883 --> 00:10:05.202
campaign structure in shopping on pmax.

00:10:05.203 --> 00:10:09.472
Because if you're splitting if you're already splitting your

00:10:09.473 --> 00:10:13.616
shopping campaigns in margins then splitting them again and

00:10:13.617 --> 00:10:16.336
you're really splitting your data too much.

00:10:16.337 --> 00:10:17.840
So you can't that you usually just have

00:10:17.841 --> 00:10:20.648
one shot to split your shopping campaigns.

00:10:20.649 --> 00:10:24.728
So by using that one shot you have for margins

00:10:24.729 --> 00:10:27.632
is just not the best way to get better performance.

00:10:27.633 --> 00:10:29.552
So based on this, if you have a lot

00:10:29.553 --> 00:10:32.480
of different brands, a lot of different categories with

00:10:32.481 --> 00:10:35.456
different margins, I highly, highly recommend to look at

00:10:35.457 --> 00:10:38.932
profit metrics or custom code profit tracking yourself.

00:10:38.933 --> 00:10:40.380
It is doable.

00:10:40.381 --> 00:10:42.240
Profit metrics skips all that.

00:10:42.780 --> 00:10:45.004
Second thing, implement it into your account.

00:10:45.005 --> 00:10:46.316
I have another video on how

00:10:46.317 --> 00:10:48.500
to actually implement profit based bidding.

00:10:48.501 --> 00:10:50.556
And the third, try to try to

00:10:50.557 --> 00:10:52.324
play around with the with the targets.

00:10:52.325 --> 00:10:55.076
Just make sure you use something like blended roas

00:10:55.077 --> 00:10:57.756
or you look at new customer acquisition data or

00:10:57.757 --> 00:10:59.644
something else as a secondary data point.

00:10:59.645 --> 00:11:01.276
Again, don't just look at your

00:11:01.277 --> 00:11:03.132
numbers in your Google Ads account.

